
<p><b>This widget is depricated by <%= link_to "the iframe widget", url_for(:action => :iframe_widget, :controller => :link_bar, :only_path => false) %>.</b></p>

<p>You can use the following code to include the C4C Link Bar in a webpage (it will be prepended to the body).</p>

<p>In the url you may adjust the page_wrapper_width parameter to match your page wrapper width.</p>

<p>
  You may also set the active tab by setting the active_tab_id parameter to the ID of the tab corresponding to the active tab.<br/>
  e.g. link_bar_tab_1 or link_bar_tab_2 etc.
</p>

<strong>Wordpress instructions:</strong> create a new Widget Widget and copy and paste this code into it</p>

<p style="margin:1em; padding:1em; border:solid black 2px;">
  <small style="font-family:monospace;">

    <%=h render :partial => "/link_bar/link_bar_css", :locals => {:page_wrapper_width => @page_wrapper_width} %>

    <%=h "<script type='text/javascript'>" %>

      jQuery(document).ready(function() {
        jQuery("body").prepend("
          <%=h render :partial => "/link_bar/link_bar_html", :locals => {:staff => @show_staff, :active_tab_id => @active_tab_id} %>
        ");
      });

    <%=h "</script>" %>

    <%=h render :partial => "/link_bar/link_bar_js" %>

  </small>
</p>
